==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mangonize
<hw>Man"go*nize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mangonizare</ets>, fr. <ets>mango</ets> a dealer in slaves or
wares, to which he tries to give an appearance of greater value by
decking them out or furbishing them up.]</ety> <def>To furbish up for
sale; to set off to advantage.</def> <mark>[Obs. or R.]</mark>
<rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

